During the ceremony, Obama will also receive a gold medal, a diploma and a check of ten million Swedish crowns (about 1.1 million euros).
He intends to make a donation to charity, but he has not yet decided which.
His program will then lead him and his wife to a banquet including, in addition to the king and the queen of Norway, the head of the government and 250 other guests.
Obama was rather reluctant at the beginning.
He mentioned, for example, the feeling that he did not deserve it fully.
He also repeated several times that it is not a price for him alone, but for all those who defend the same values as him.
