Manually calculate the cost of repairing between €20,000 and €30 000, including the parts and the work hand can take two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the assistance of the most recent computer tools, this would be a matter of minutes.
That is why almost 100% of experts use this type of systems.
Providers of services and solutions for disaster assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting information provided by manufacturers, then treating them and offering them to their clients in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audex, of the North American Solar Group, is the leading company; 80% of the estimates are made with its products.
Other competing companies in the field of evaluation tools and sector information development are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Work with the data provided by manufacturers is far from easy.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Audatex's commercial director, the company in Spain has 63 manufacturers and importers, each providing information in a different format.
Moreover, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, so that over the past five years, more versions, variants and motorizations have been launched only during the previous fifteen years.
When a new car leaves the market, these companies get to work.
This is a very hard work, as each of the thousands of pieces of the vehicle must be cataloged and their price entered.
In addition, there is a "smart" graphic image of each model on which you can click on the different parts of a car.
If this is a model sold massively, work can be prepared within a week if the process progresses very quickly.
